
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gnome-help` baraye baz kardane rahnama-ye (help) desktop GNOME estefade mishavad. In rahnama etela'at dar morede estefade az GNOME va barname-haye motealeq be aan ra faraaham mikonad.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gnome-help`  --> 🚀 Baz kardane rahnama-ye asli (main help viewer)
    🔹 `gnome-help URL`  --> 🌐 Baz kardane safhe-ye rahnama ba address interneti (URL) moshakhas
    🔹 `gnome-help topic`  --> 📚 Baz kardane rahnama baraye yek mavzooe khas (topic)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**
    
    $ gnome-help
   
    🔹 Baz kardane rahnama-ye GNOME.
    
    $ gnome-help network
   
    🔹 Baz kardane rahnama baraye mavzooe "network".

✅ **Mesal sade:**
    
    $ gnome-help preferences
   
    🔹 Baz kardane rahnama dar bakhshe "preferences" baraye tanzimat va tarjihate GNOME.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gnome-help` command is used to open the GNOME desktop help system. This help system provides information on using GNOME and its related applications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gnome-help`  --> 🚀 Opens the main help viewer.
    🔹 `gnome-help URL`  --> 🌐 Opens the help page at the specified URL.
    🔹 `gnome-help topic`  --> 📚 Opens the help for a specific topic.

🛠 **Examples:**
    
    $ gnome-help
    
    🔹 Opens the GNOME help viewer.

    $ gnome-help network
    
    🔹 Opens the help documentation for the "network" topic.

✅ **Simple Example:**
    
    $ gnome-help preferences
    
    🔹 Opens the help documentation in the "preferences" section, related to GNOME settings and preferences.
